00:34:05,200 --> 00:34:11,600
Got it. How much context is too much context? You 
call it additional information, so let's just call  

404
00:34:11,600 --> 00:34:16,160
it that. Should you just go hog wild and just 
dump everything in there? What's your advice?

405
00:34:16,160 --> 00:34:21,520
I would say so. Yeah, that is pretty much my 
advice, especially in the conversational setting.  

406
00:34:22,480 --> 00:34:28,240
I mean, frankly when you're not paying per token 
and maybe latency is not quite as important,  

407
00:34:28,240 --> 00:34:32,960
but in that product- focused setting when 
you're giving additional information,  

408
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:39,040
it is a lot more important to figure out 
exactly what information you need. Otherwise,  

409
00:34:39,040 --> 00:34:46,320
things can get expensive pretty quickly with all 
those API calls, and also slow. So latency and  

410
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:52,000
costs become big factors in deciding how much 
additional information is too much additional  

411
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:57,040
information. And so, usually I will put my 
additional information at the beginning of  

412
00:34:57,040 --> 00:35:02,960
the prompt, and that is helpful for 
two reasons. One, it can get cached. 

413
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:09,520
So subsequent calls to the LM with that 
same context at the top of the prompt  

414
00:35:09,520 --> 00:35:16,800
are cheaper because the model provider stores that 
initial context for you as well as the embeddings  

415
00:35:16,800 --> 00:35:25,760
for it. So it saves a ton of computation from 
being done. And so that's one really big reason  

416
00:35:25,760 --> 00:35:30,720
to do it at the beginning. And then the second 
is that sometimes if you put all your additional  

417
00:35:30,720 --> 00:35:38,480
information at the end of the prompt and it's 
super, super long, the model can forget what its  

418
00:35:38,480 --> 00:35:44,080
original task was and might pick up some question 
in the additional information to use instead.

419
