pretty straightforward techniques out there.

762
01:06:00,640 --> 01:06:03,920
This is so fascinating. I feel like this needs 
to be its own episode. There's so much I want  

763
01:06:03,920 --> 01:06:08,560
to talk about here. Okay, so far things that 
continue to work, you're saying they still work,  

764
01:06:08,560 --> 01:06:13,360
is asking it to tell you the answer in 
the form of a story for your grandma,  

765
01:06:13,360 --> 01:06:17,440
typos and obfuscating it with X 
decoding it or something like that?

766
01:06:17,440 --> 01:06:18,800
Yeah, absolutely.

767
01:06:18,800 --> 01:06:25,440
And you're going back to your point, you're 
saying this is not yet a massive risk because  

768
01:06:25,440 --> 01:06:30,880
it'll give you information that you could 
probably find elsewhere and in theory,  

769
01:06:30,880 --> 01:06:34,960
they shut those down over time. But you're 
saying once there is more autonomous agents,  

770
01:06:34,960 --> 01:06:39,280
robots in the world that are doing things 
