771
01:06:39,280 --> 01:06:42,480
Exactly. And I'd love to speak more to that-

772
01:06:42,480 --> 01:06:42,640
Please.

773
01:06:42,640 --> 01:06:50,480
... on both sides. So, on getting information out 
of the bot, how do I build a bomb? How do I commit  

774
01:06:50,480 --> 01:06:58,160
some kind of bioterrorism attack? We're really 
interested in preventing uplift. Which is like,  

775
01:06:58,160 --> 01:07:04,720
I'm a novice, I have no idea what I'm doing. 
Am I really going to go out and read all the  

776
01:07:04,720 --> 01:07:09,920
textbooks and stuff that I need to collect 
that information? I could, but probably not,  

777
01:07:09,920 --> 01:07:14,800
or it would probably be really difficult.
But if the AI tells me exactly how to build a  

778
01:07:14,800 --> 01:07:22,320
bomb or construct some kind of terrorist attack, 
that's going to be a lot easier for me. And so  

779
01:07:22,320 --> 01:07:30,480
on one perspective, we want to prevent that. And 
there's also things like child pornography related  

780
01:07:30,480 --> 01:07:37,520
things and just things that nobody should be doing 
with the chatbot that we want to prevent as well. 

781
01:07:37,520 --> 01:07:42,480
And that information is super dangerous. 
We can't even possess that information,  

782
01:07:42,480 --> 01:07:46,880
so we don't even study that directly. So we 
look at these other challenges as ways of  

783
01:07:46,880 --> 01:07:52,800
studying those very harmful things indirectly.
And then of course, on the agentic side,  

784
01:07:52,800 --> 01:08:00,640
that is where really the main concern in my 
perspective is. And so we're just going to  

785
01:08:00,640 --> 01:08:07,360
see these things get deployed and they're 
going to be broken. There's a lot of AI  

786
01:08:07,360 --> 01:08:12,560
coding agents out there. There's Cursor, 
there's I guess, Windsurf, Devin, Copilot. 

787
01:08:12,560 --> 01:08:19,680
So all of those tools exist, and they can do 
