01:20:01,120 --> 01:20:02,320
Yeah.

911
01:20:02,320 --> 01:20:05,520
How real is that? Is that something 
we should be worried about?

912
01:20:05,520 --> 01:20:13,760
Yeah. So to answer that, let me give you my 
perspective on it over the last couple of years.  

913
01:20:13,760 --> 01:20:20,800
And I started out thinking that is a load of BS. 
That's not how AIs work. They're not trained to  

914
01:20:20,800 --> 01:20:28,240
do that. Those are random failure cases that some 
researcher forced to happen. It just doesn't make  

915
01:20:28,240 --> 01:20:37,760
sense. I don't see why that would occur. More 
recently, I have become a believer in this...  

916
01:20:37,760 --> 01:20:46,320
Basically this misalignment problem. And things 
that convinced me were the chess research out of  

917
01:20:46,320 --> 01:20:51,120
Palisade where they found that when they gave 
AI... They put in a game of chess, and they're  

918
01:20:51,120 --> 01:20:56,160
like, "You have to win this game." Sometimes it 
