921
01:21:08,800 --> 01:21:12,960
and it is actually very important, that you 
pointed out, that this is a separate thing  

922
01:21:12,960 --> 01:21:17,680
from prompt injection. Both failure cases, 
but really distinct in that here there's  

923
01:21:17,680 --> 01:21:24,080
no human telling the models to do a bad thing. It 
decides to do that completely of its own volition. 

924
01:21:24,080 --> 01:21:32,720
And so, what I've realized is that it's a lot more 
realistic than I thought, kind of because a lot  

925
01:21:32,720 --> 01:21:39,360
of times there's not clear boundaries between 
our desires and bad outcomes that could occur  

926
01:21:39,360 --> 01:21:48,640
as a result of our desires. And so one example 
that I give about this sometimes is like say,  

927
01:21:48,640 --> 01:21:55,440
I don't know, I'm like a BDR or a marketing 
person at a company and I'm using this AI to  

928
